here i dont see the varaibles what i mentioned in docker file y because after creation we can't access

ARG vs ENV:
Env varaibles can be accesible at image build time and container both.
ARG is only accessed at the time of image creation.
You can use ARG instruction before FROM in some special case i.e., to supply the version to the base image

i can override below values by running command 
From almalinux:9
ARG course="Devops " \
    Duration="120hrs" 
RUN echo "course: $course, duration: $duration"
CMD ["sleep", "100"]

docker build -t arg:v1 --build-arg course=docker .
root@a20b57bd2898 /]# deepika@ngdocker build -t arg:v1 --build-arg course=docker .ild-arg course=docker .
