changed from above to below why because maybe in future almalinux version updates to 10 so no need to change manually to come here, we can update like below.
ARG version
From almalinux:${version}
ARG course="Devops " \
    Duration="120hrs" 
RUN echo "course: $course, duration: $duration"
CMD ["sleep", "100"]
docker build -t arg:v1 --build-arg course=docker --build-arg version=8
it installs version 8

if you forget to mention in above command it shows errors and it better to update some default value if we forget also its not create a problem.
ARG version
From almalinux:${version:-9}
ARG course="Devops " \
    Duration="120hrs" 
RUN echo "course: $course, duration: $duration"
CMD ["sleep", "100"]

